title: Thursday night football highlighted by Palm Beach Gardens district championship
text:
Thursday night football highlighted by Palm Beach Gardens district championship 
By Matt Lincoln/CBS12PALM BEACH GARDENS, Fla (CBS12) - Palm Beach Gardens scored two touchdowns within minutes from each other in the third quarter, and that was enough to topple Wellington 14-9 Thursday night, effectively giving them the district championship. The Gators trailed the Wolverines 3-0 at the half. In the third quarter, Vondarius Cowan blocked a punt that was covered up by Justin Taylor in the end zone. Then leading 7-3, Devon Studstill took two snaps from the wildcat and scored the only offensive touchdown Gardens would need. The Gators will host a first round playoff game.Palm Beach County gave students the day off Friday, so some schools decided to move their games to Thursday.
